docs/modules/frontend.md:8:| `components/SessionSidebar.tsx` | Project Registry-driven project/space tree sidebar. It loads projects from `/api/projects` instead of synthesizing them from sessions, lazy-loads linked sessions for the selected project space, hides YPI Studio child audit sessions from ordinary root history by default while showing them as nested Studio audit rows under visible parents, shows exact-cwd legacy unassigned sessions separately, keeps WorkTree actions available for worktree spaces, and includes archive/unarchive actions plus the integrated file explorer with a resizable session/explorer split. **Project/space selection** has been replaced from an inline dropdown to a compact top switch button (`选择项目空间` when empty, or `ProjectName / SpaceName` when selected). Clicking the button opens `ProjectSpaceSwitchDialog` for layered (left project list → right space list) browsing, search, and add-project flows inside a viewport-level modal dialog. The `SessionSidebar` owns all project/space state and callbacks (registration from manual path, OS directory picker, Git clone, default directory) and passes them into the dialog as props; the dialog is purely a UI shell that calls back to the sidebar's existing `upsertProjectAndSelectMainSpace()`, `handleDirectoryPicker()`, `commitCustomPath()`, `handleGitCloneSubmit()`, etc. The sidebar header displays current project name / space subtitle / WorkTree badge; WorkTree archive/delete remains available by right-clicking the selected switch button or a WorkTree row inside the dialog. Add-project forms (manual path, Git clone) are rendered inside the dialog with mutually exclusive toggles; empty registry onboarding renders directly in the dialog with large primary buttons for `Add project folder…` / `Add project path…` / `Add project from Git…` / `Use default directory`. The dialog closes on successful registration/clone and selects the returned main space; on failure the current project is unchanged. Main spaces without a custom display name render as `主空间` while keeping `spaceId: "main"`; the selected space header subtitle shows `空间：...` plus the current Git branch or WorkTree branch/base status, appends path-missing state when needed, and keeps full path/status details in the hover/focus tooltip. WorkTree badges remain compact (`WT` plus branch) with a tooltip for branch and base/unknown state. Session, Studio child, hover-action, delete-confirmation, and archived rows keep title/metadata content on single non-wrapping lines and ellipsize long text at narrow sidebar widths. **WorkTree archive/delete flow:** `confirmWorktreeAction()` optimistically merges the API response's `archivedSpaces` into local project state so the worktree space disappears immediately, then refreshes projects in the background. If the currently-selected space was the archived/deleted one, fallback preference is: (1) `main` space of the same project, (2) any other active non-missing space in that project, (3) API-provided `fallbackCwd`, (4) null. Deleted session ids are forwarded via `onSessionDeleted`. The sidebar **centralizes project and space context menu state** through `ProjectSpaceContextMenuState` (targeting a specific project or project+space pair). Context menu callbacks (`handleDialogProjectContextMenu`, `handleDialogSpaceContextMenu`) bridge dialog right-click events into the sidebar state so that edit/star/archive/WorkTree-delete actions operate on the right-clicked target, not just the currently selected workspace. **Space drag-reorder** is handled by `handleReorderSpaces` which optimistically updates local state and calls `PATCH /api/projects/[projectId]/spaces`, rolling back to pre-drag project state on failure. **Top workspace menu and metadata dialog** labels have been unified to "星标/取消星标" for both projects and spaces; the metadata dialog distinguishes the two with contextual hints ("星标项目优先排序" for projects vs "仅用于标记，不影响空间排序" for spaces). |
